National Super League giants Shabana’s recent woes deepened on Sunday after they lost 1-0 against bottom side Soy United at the Migori Stadium to effective bow out of contention for promotion. Shabana goalkeeper Elix Otieno’s gaffe in the first half that handed Soy the lead was the major highlight of the game as they held on to win and complete a double over their hosts following their 2-1 in the reverse fixture. Their latest triumph will give the Xavier Francis-coached side hope that they can mount a serious survival fight as they are five points adrift of safety with nine games to go. As for the home side, Shabana, the match presented an opportunity to hold on to their slim chances of challenging for a promotion playoff berth buy their display offered little hope to their faithful. They trailed 1-0 into the break against a side that lost 4-0 against Kenya Police last week and could not device a way past Soy’s rear-guard in the second half. Head coach Robert Ojienda made no bones in his scathing assessment of the team’s recent poor show. Also Read: “The boys have lost focus and today’s game was no different. “We are officially out of contention for promotion and I hope this will get the pressure off the players as we approach our last seven games.” His opposite number Francis Xavier remained optimistic of their survival chances, as he urged his players not to let their feet of the gas. “We have struggled recently and we are ranked at number last on the log. Today we played well and I hope this will give us believe that we can survive.”  Saturday Results Modern Coast Rangers 2-1 Gusii Migori Youth 1-2 Vihiga Bullets Talanta 1-1 Coast Stima Video Of The Day: KEMRI scientists examine safety of anti-malarial drugs in first trimester of pregnancy